para.p:
This is essentially the same proof given by Charikar, Guruswami, and Wirth [CGW1, CGW2];
we repeat it here to keep the paper self-contained. If ≥x⁢uz-1α,
then for each ∈w∪{u}T, we have

Math.tex:
\displaystyle\sum_{w\in N^{+}(z)\cap T_{i}}x_{wz}+\sum_{\mathclap{w\in N^{-}(z%
)\cap T_{i}}}(1-x_{wz})\geq\sum_{{w\in N^{+}(z)\cap T_{i}}}(x_{u_{j}z}-\frac{1%
}{14}-x_{uiw})+\sum_{\mathclap{w\in N^{-}(z)\cap T_{i}}}(1-x_{u_{j}z}-\frac{1}%
{14}-x_{u_{i}w})

\displaystyle\sum_{w\in N^{+}(z)\cap T_{i}}x_{wz}+\sum_{\mathclap{w\in N^{-}(z%
)\cap T_{i}}}(1-x_{wz})\geq\sum_{{w\in N^{+}(z)\cap T_{i}}}(x_{u_{j}z}-\frac{1%
}{14}-x_{uiw})+\sum_{\mathclap{w\in N^{-}(z)\cap T_{i}}}(1-x_{u_{j}z}-\frac{1}%
{14}-x_{u_{i}w})
